Description:
Boutique Bliss with Light and Style!
In an impeccably-maintained block (one of only four), this secluded townhouse presents a wonderful low-maintenance lifestyle opportunity with its indoor/outdoor space, quality enhancements throughout and outstanding urban convenience. Bathed in northerly light, the home's impressive interior comprises two bedrooms (extra-large master) both with built-in robes, contemporary-style central bathroom and additional powder room (second WC). Add to this a sunny lounge leading through to the modern kitchen/meals complete with soft-close drawers, tiled splashbacks and dishwasher. Other stand-out features include an under-stair pantry/storage area and spacious attic storeroom, full-size laundry, solid timber floors, panel heating and ducted evaporative cooling. Step outside to discover an oversized rear courtyard with established gardens and extensive paving, plus the added advantage of a single lock-up garage. Well south of Bell Street and within the Strathmore Secondary College zone, it's walking distance to Melville Road trams and Munro Street buses, close to Shore Reserve and popular primary schools, Coburg Station, Sydney Road eateries and renowned retail precinct as well as easy Citylink access. Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Low Maintenance Living in the Heart of Coburg
More than meets the eye, this home is set to impress with its low maintenance living & instant access to all Coburg's amenities. Whether you're a first home buyer, looking to downsize or add to your investment portfolio this character filled home is a must see!
Beyond its charming facade, this home offers 2 good size bedrooms (master with semi-ensuite), well appointed kitchen, adjoining meals area, large family room & a private low maintenance courtyard.
Further features include remote garage, high ceilings, cooling, heating, roller shutters & much more.
Perfectly located within walking distance to Bell Street, public transport, local specialty shops & also close to many primary schools & sporting facilities, This is an opportunity not to be missed. Call now!

Description:
'Moreland Park' - More Than You Imagined
EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST CLOSE TUESDAY, 25 JUNE AT 5.00PM (Unless sold prior)
A very rare buying opportunity to acquire - 2 x prime income producing properties, on one title with great future potential and subdivision possibilities (STCA/STPA) on a vast allotment of approx. 2097 m2 of prime land.
Property One - An extraordinary Boom Style double fronted Victorian Italianate house. This historic home and landmark built as the principal residence of Montague Dare within the precinct he helped develop: Coburg's most prestigious estate - Moreland Park. Benefitting from mature gardens, the property retains amazing features including high pressed metal ceilings, grand ballrooms, timber fretwork, ornate fire surrounds and other grand details. Currently leased as four separate residences, each with one or two bedrooms, kitchen, bathroom and a large defining living space.
Property Two - A two level Apartment building built in the 1960s & consisting of
4 x 2 bedroom spacious apartments offered in good condition with excellent natural light and generous properties. Each apartment enjoys two large bedrooms, separate living & dining rooms, kitchen, bathroom & laundry and share 4 carport spaces. 2 of the apartments also feature balconies & sunrooms. Located moments to Egan Reserve by the Merri Creek, Nicholson Street trams, cafes and schools, and a quick drive to buzzing Sydney Road. A wonderful property with exciting and versatile investment possibilities. First time offered in over 60 years.

Description:
SOLD by Team Stewart
On a substantial block of land 569m2 approx. and complete with two entrance points, this home presents an exciting opportunity for those looking to renovate/extend or completely start anew (STCA). Ideally located with local schools, shops and public transport all close by, would make this the perfect home. Contact the team today.
PROPERTY SPECIFICATIONS:
House. Built in 1930'3 approx.
Land size 569m2 approx. Building size of 19sq approx.
- KITCHEN: Timber cabinetry with laminate benchtops. One-piece S/S gas cooktop and electric oven, double S/S kitchen sink, pantry with cupboard space, breakfast bench and tiled flooring
- MEALS: Open plan area with tiled flooring
- DINING: Separate formal area with tiled flooring
- LIVING: Separate formal area with carpeted flooring
- BEDROOMS: Three double bedrooms. Master with robe, all with carpeted flooring
- BATHROOM: 1200mm shower, separate bathtub, single vanity with cupboard space, separate toiled area and tiled flooring
- LAUNDRY: Separate area with double trough, built-in cupboard and bench space
- HEAT/COOL: Ducted heating
- OUTDOORS: Pergola area, landscaped gardens with lawn and garden beds, established trees, including many fruit trees
- ADDITIONAL: High ceilings, Holland blinds, curtains and gas HWS
- PARKING: Two single garages, one via rear lane-way plus driveway space for up to 3 more cars
- POTENTIAL RENT:440 $ - $480 p/w approx.
- ZONING: General Residential Zone - Schedule 1
LOCATION BENEFITS:
- Located near Sydney Road, Sussex St, Cumberland Rd and Gaffney St Shopping Strip
- Close to Coburg and Batman Train Station, parks and local primary schools
- Coburg is located approx. 8 km's North of the CBD with terrific City Link, Ring Road, major arterial roads and airport access
PREFERRED SALE TERMS:
DEPOSIT:
- 10%
SETTLEMENT:
- 30/45/60 days
Buy this unique home today by calling one of our friendly team members. It won't last long!

Description:
Enhanced Character in Lifestyle Locale
Combining rich character with modern updates, this three bedroom, two bathroom, 1920s residence is zoned to Strathmore College and close to a range of amenities and tempting eateries. Greeting the street with colourful roses and a Californian Bungalow style facade, the home welcomes visitors with leadlight. The floor plan leads from an entrance area to a lounge with decorative features, including ceiling detail and a fireplace with carved timber mantelpiece. A range of stainless steel appliances, encompassing a freestanding stove with gas cooktop and electric oven, rangehood and Asko dishwasher, meets with timber counters and good storage space in the kitchen, and the renovated abode also offers a covered rear deck and gardens. Each of the two bathrooms includes a bath, with the stunning rear bathroom flaunting an impressive contemporary transformation. Hosting a frameless rainfall shower, freestanding bath, toilet and floating vanity, the tranquil room quickly invokes feelings of relaxation. Polished floorboards, reverse cycle ducted heating/refrigerated cooling, a wide garage and rear right of way round out major features.
Local favourite Good Times Cafe is within a short walk, as are trams, buses, schools, parks and shops, while a long list of popular nearby eateries includes The Post Office Hotel.

Description:
Clinker Brick Charm, Position And Potential
Presenting an exciting opportunity to modernise whilst retaining character, this near original two bedroom clinker brink home sits on a deep block and offers excellent renovation/extension potential (STCA). Beyond a charming exterior finds a welcoming entry hall leading to a spacious lounge featuring high ceilings, decorative plasterwork, picture rails and an open fireplace. Towards the rear is a serviceable kitchen with meals area and updated cooking appliances. A neatly adjoining sunroom/sitting area opens to an undercover alfresco zone and generous back garden highlighted by wood-fired pizza oven, water feature and low maintenance surrounds. Two well scaled bedrooms present built-in-robes and a myriad of original features. They are served by a classic bathroom, separate laundry and toilet. Includes polished hardwood floors, ducted heating, "Healthy Home" ventilated heating system, rain water tank and off street parking. Located in a quiet pocket, the home is just minutes from cosmopolitan Sydney Road shops, cafes, Coburg Market, St Fidelis primary, Coburg West primary, trains, trams and buses.

Description:
Renovated haven in tightly-held locale
Recently renovated with sustainability as the main focus, and superbly situated in a tightly-held pocket, this naturally bright and enticing three bedroom, two bathroom, c.1924 bungalow includes the bonus of a modern and self-contained unit at the rear. Welcoming in abundant natural light, the kitchen/meals/living is spacious, full of character and equipped for cooking with gas. High ceilings, double glazing, high rating wall and roof insulation, passive heating and cooling and flyscreens work towards energy efficiency. Bedrooms feature sound insulation and can all comfortably accommodate double beds and bathrooms include an ensuite. Featuring a verandah, cathedral ceiling and spa bathroom, the unit has been thoughtfully designed too. Completed by a front garden and ample parking, this tranquil family haven is positioned to please mere seconds to Merri Creek and trams, close to shops, schools, cafes and dining precincts.

Description:
A Timeless Classic Family Home!
Nestled in a quiet tree lined street is this wonderful solid brick Californian Bungalow style family home. This timeless classic has been extended and offers ample living and outdoor space, making this a perfect opportunity for the new lucky family. Perfectly positioned and only a short stroll to schools, transport and playgrounds it's also situated near Coburg Market and Sydney Road. This is one opportunity you don't want to pass up!
PROPERTY SPECIFICATIONS:
- Solid brick Californian bungalow home built in the 1920's (approx.)
- Land size 456m2 (approx.)
- Three spacious bedrooms with timber flooring to bedrooms 1 & 2 and carpeted flooring to bedroom 3
- Updated timber kitchen complimented with stainless steel appliances including 600mm oven/grill and 900mm 4 burner gas cooker & rangehood, pantry and a great amount of cupboard & bench space
- Three generous living zones, a generously sized sun filled formal lounge, a meals area adjoining the kitchen and a 2nd additional living/dining space which can also be converted into a 4th bedroom
- Centrally positioned bathroom offering bathtub, shower, single vanity, toilet & bidet
- Outside, a great low maintenance backyard perfect for entertaining
- A side driveway leads you to a double lock up garage and has capacity for 3+ off street car spaces
- Complimented with many extras including: ducted heating, evaporative cooling, 2nd toilet, kitchenette in the garage with sink and cooktop, alarm system, ducted vacuum, video intercom system & window shutters
- POTENTIAL RENTAL RETURN: $550 - $580 p/w (approx.)
LOCATION BENEFITS:
- Located within close distance to Sydney Road shopping strip, parks and local schools
- Close to Coburg & Moreland train stations and Melville Road & Sydney Road tram lines
- Coburg is located 9km's north of the CBD with terrific CityLink and airport access
Make sure you place this on top of your shopping list!

Description:
Personality And Potential On Some 367m2
Super neat and strategically positioned close to Batman station, Coburg Market and Sydney Road right now, this enticing 3 bedroom home is an intelligent investment that promises rewarding renovation or new home site scope, STCA, on some 367m2 when you're ready. Generous living/dining spaces, a separate kitchen and sun-room deliver complete current day comfort and engaging character that's complemented by a central bathroom and a large laundry. Original floorboards, gas heating, high ceilings, retro personality and outstanding presentation further enhance the present day proportions while the garden's size, plentiful side drive parking and a lock-up garage provide proof of the allotment's appeal - and its exceptional future potential. Capture this property today and maximize the opportunity tomorrow in a location that's so rich in lifestyle attractions, including Harmony Park, Coburg North Primary School and convenient proximity to cafes and trams.

Description:
UNDER OFFER
Rich in heritage detail, this delightful four bedroom, two bathroom Californian Bungalow also offers a studio/workshop with home office possibilities. Set amidst manicured gardens, the home's extended layout comprises elegant fretwork hallway, with original timber paneling, plate rails and high ceilings, formal dining room, highlighted by sparkling chandelier, sunroom and light filled lounge featuring lead light bay window, Baltic pine floorboards and one of two working open fireplaces. Enjoying glorious garden vistas, a timber kitchen/meals showcases panoramic views across the rear gardens, electric cooking appliances and breakfast bar. Includes paved alfresco, walk-in/built-in-robes, charming bathrooms, split-system air conditioner, ducted heating, solar electricity, rain water tanks, garden sheds and garage/additional off street parking. Opposite parklands, near schools, Sydney Road shops, Coburg Market, trains, trams and buses at the door.

Description:
UNDER OFFER
Modern townhouse living is at its best when positioned amongst the vibrant cafes, trams and shopping of Nicholson Street, Lygon Street & Sydney Road, enjoys easy access to Merri Creek trails and presents spacious modern interiors. This three bedroom two bathroom townhouse does just that, offering a low maintenance lifestyle of absolute convenience and style. Serenely positioned, this property showcases free flowing lounge and dining serviced by a stylish granite topped kitchen featuring as new stainless steel appliances, and opening to a private easy care garden. Double bedrooms, one with study nook, share two stylish bathrooms, master with ensuite, while a separate laundry, heating, excellent storage and car space complete this home. Set in a community minded complex near Northcote Golf Course, schools and Moreland Station.

Description:
Under Offer
Entry-Level Excellence in the Heart of Coburg! Tucked away in a secure well-maintained complex (1 of 19), this top-floor apartment is sure to make an impression with its immaculate presentation, elevated outlook and unrivalled inner-urban ease. Light-filled interior comprises two generous bedrooms (both with built-in robes), stylish central bathroom and adjoining laundry. Add to this a spacious lounge with city skyline views leading through to the contemporary-style kitchen/meals area complete with dishwasher and stainless steel cooking appliances. Along with a wide entrance foyer with linen cupboards, panel heating and intercom system, it also includes an undercover parking space on title via gated driveway (remote-controlled). A brilliant location in cosmopolitan Coburg, walking distance to Sydney Road trams, cafes and restaurants, close to local schools, Coburg Station and the area's renowned shopping precinct. Move straight in rent straight out - a winning decision either way!

Description:
STUNNING RESIDENCE IN PENTRIDGE VILLAGE !
Pocketed in the highly sought after tree-lined streets in the Pentridge Village lies this stunning residence complete and ready to be secured by the lucky purchaser. Sitting high and grand with manicured gardens front and back. Walk in and be welcomed by a stunning entry with high 10' ceilings, quality floorboards throughout, formal lounge room with a gas log fireplace, an elegant spacious stone top kitchen with a 900mm s/s app with breakfast bar bench and walk in pantry with a large adjoining meals area plus a separate family room. Walk straight out to your breathtaking undercover timber deck,perfect for entertaining with a low maintenance yard for your kids and pets. 4 bedrooms up on offer (master with WIR, full ensuite and a private balcony with fantastic views of Merri Merri Creek with the Merri Creek Trail), bir's, home office, central bathroom and laundry. Extras include: ducted heating, ducted refrigerated cooling, dishwasher, split system upstairs, downlights, alarm system, large 2 car remote garage with internal access.
All this within close proximity to the Merri Creek Trail, Coburg parkland, Sydney Road shops/ cafes and restaurants, public and private school plus public transport !
Don't miss out !
Settlement: 30, 60 or 90 days

facebook.com/malek.younan.raywhite
